Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Peel and dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. (TIP: For speedier spud prep, skip the peeling.) Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

== Roasted Carrots ==

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil; cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with @sour cream{6%tablespoon} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Caramelized Onions ==

While potatoes cook, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tablespoon} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1%teaspoon} and a splash of water; cook until caramelized, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Bavette Steak ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Mushroom Sauce ==

Add @butter{1%tablespoon} and mushrooms to pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @beef demi-glace{1}. Add ¼ cup water. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer.

Stir in @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice steak against the grain.

Divide potatoes, carrots, and steak between plates. Top potatoes with caramelized onion. Top steak with mushroom sauce and serve.